[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m189[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m190[0m[39m:                    else[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m191[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m192[0m[39m:                        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m code may have to be changed in something better, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaybe new token type[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m193[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m194[0m[39m:                        return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, Token.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m195[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m196[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:                else if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCharacter.isWhitespace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m198[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:                    skip = true;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m201[0m[39m:                else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"NULL byte in font, skipped"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:                    skip = true;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:                else[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:                    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m regular character: try parse as number[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:                    Token number = [0m[1;35mtryReadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:                    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumber != null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:                        return number;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:                    else[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:                        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m otherwise this must be a name[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:                        String name = [0m[1;35mreadRegular[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:                        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mname == null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[39m:                            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the stream is corrupt[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m:                            throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Could not read [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mtoken at position "[0m[39m +[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m:                                                           [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m225[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:                        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mname.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"RD"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mname.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"-|"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:                            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m return the next CharString instead[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:                            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprevToken != null && [0m[1;35mprevToken.getKind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mToken.INTEGER[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:                            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:                                return [0m[1;35mreadCharString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mprevToken.intValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:                            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:                            else[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m235[0m[39m:                            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m236[0m[39m:                                throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"expected INTEGER before [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m-| or RD"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m237[0m[39m:                            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m238[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m239[0m[39m:                        else[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m240[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m241[0m[39m:                            return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname, Token.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m242[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m243[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m244[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m245[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m246[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m247[0m[39m:        while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m248[0m[39m:        return null;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m249[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Issue[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBased on the evaluation report and code analysis, the timeout occurs in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when processing a maliciously crafted Type1 font [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontaining an extremely large sequence of consecutive whitespace or NULL bytes. The[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue is an algorithmic complexity DoS vulnerability where:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The inner `while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` loop processes characters one-by-one[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. For whitespace [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m199[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and NULL bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m204[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the `skip` flag is set but [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing continues[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. With millions/billions of consecutive whitespace/NULL characters, this loop runs[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor an extremely long time[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The timeout occurs after ~[0m[1;36m28.68[0m[39m seconds of CPU-intensive processing[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is NOT a traditional infinite loop, but rather a pathologically long-running [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop when processing adversarial input.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Core Insights from Code Analysis[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Existing Protection Patterns**: The codebase already has similar protections:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `PfbParser` limits total font size to 100MB [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MAX_LENGTH = 100_000_000`[0m[1;39m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `BaseParser` limits number parsing with `MAX_LENGTH_LONG`[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `DamagedFontException` is used for corrupt/malformed font data[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Root Cause Location**: `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at lines [0m[1;36m197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m205[0m[39m where [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitespace and NULL bytes set `skip = true` without any iteration limit[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Critical Logic to Preserve**:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The lexer must still skip legitimate whitespace between tokens[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Comments [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m131[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m must continue to be processed[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing token types and parsing logic must remain functional[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `skip` flag mechanism is used to skip whitespace between tokens[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Attack Vector**: A Type1 font segment with a valid header followed by millions[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof whitespace/NULL bytes passes initial validation but causes timeout during lexing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add a Consecutive Skip Counter[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd a class-level counter to track consecutive skipped characters in `Type1Lexer`:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate int consecutiveSkipCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate static final int MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS = [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Reasonable limit[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: After the existing instance variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m54[0m[39m, after `private[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mint openParens = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Justification**: This follows the pattern used in `BaseParser` for limiting [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsed content length. A limit of [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m consecutive skipped characters is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreasonable because:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Legitimate Type1 fonts don't have millions of consecutive whitespace[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This allows for legitimate formatting with generous margins[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It prevents DoS while maintaining compatibility[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Increment Counter When Skipping[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify the whitespace and NULL byte handling to increment the counter:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: In `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Lines [0m[1;36m197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m200[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhitespace handling[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melse if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCharacter.isWhitespace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    skip = true;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    consecutiveSkipCount++;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsecutiveSkipCount > MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Too many consecutive whitespace characters [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mat position "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Lines [0m[1;36m201[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m205[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL byte handling[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melse if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"NULL byte in font, skipped"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    skip = true;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    consecutiveSkipCount++;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsecutiveSkipCount > MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Too many consecutive NULL bytes at position[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Justification**: [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throws `DamagedFontException` following existing patterns [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m164[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m165[0m[39m, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Includes buffer position for debugging[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses descriptive error messages[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Limits consecutive skips to prevent DoS[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Reset Counter When Token is Returned[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReset the counter whenever a valid token is successfully read and returned:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: Before each `return` statement in `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation**: Add `consecutiveSkipCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` before each return statement in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe method:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m135[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return [0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m144[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, Token.START_ARRAY[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m148[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, Token.START_PROC[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m152[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, Token.END_ARRAY[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m156[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, Token.END_PROC[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mregular, Token.LITERAL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m174[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"<<"[0m[39m, Token.START_DICT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m180[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, Token.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m188[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[32m">>"[0m[39m, Token.END_DICT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m194[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, Token.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m214[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return number`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m232[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return [0m[1;35mreadCharString[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m241[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname, Token.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m248[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore `return null`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Justification**:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Resets the counter after successfully processing a token[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Allows unlimited whitespace across multiple tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39monly consecutive within one [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoken read[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintains existing behavior for legitimate fonts[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents false positives where whitespace is spread across multiple `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Handle Comment Processing[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mComments should NOT increment the skip counter since `[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` has its own [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounded loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbreaks on newline[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**No changes needed** for comment handling at lines [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m132[0m[39m, as comments naturally [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mterminate on newline and don't contribute to the DoS scenario.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m: Reset Counter at Start of Each readToken Call[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOptionally, reset the counter at the beginning of each outer loop iteration:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: Line [0m[1;36m122[0m[39m, after `skip = false;`[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mskip = false;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Note: consecutiveSkipCount is not reset here; it spans multiple outer loop [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m It's only reset when a token is successfully returned[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Justification**: The counter should track consecutive skips across the entire [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call, not just one outer loop iteration. This ensures protection [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst the DoS scenario.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## How This Fix Addresses the Issue[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Prevents Timeout**: Limits consecutive skipped characters to [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreventing the multi-second timeout[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserves Functionality**: Legitimate fonts can still have whitespace; the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimit is only for consecutive skips[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Follows Existing Patterns**: Uses `DamagedFontException` like other validation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailures in the same file[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Clear Error Messages**: Includes position and reason for the exception[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Side Effects**: Only affects pathological cases; normal font processing is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munaffected[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Maintains Test Compatibility**: Legitimate fonts pass through normally; only [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madversarial input is rejected[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **[0m[3;91mFalse[0m[39m Positives**: If a legitimate font has >[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m consecutive whitespace [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacters[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This is extremely unlikely; [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m is a generous limit[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Alternative**: Could increase limit to [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m if needed[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Breaking Existing Tests**: If tests use fonts with excessive whitespace[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: The limit is so high that no legitimate test should fail[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Verification**: Run existing test suite after applying fix[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance**: Additional counter checks on every skipped character[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Impact**: Negligible [0m[1;39m([0m[39msimple integer comparison[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Benefit**: Prevents catastrophic performance degradation from DoS[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `PfbParser.MAX_LENGTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m71[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Limits total font size to prevent memory [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexhaustion[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `BaseParser.MAX_LENGTH_LONG` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m65[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Limits number string length during [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Both use exceptions to signal malformed input[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix applies the same defensive programming pattern to the lexer level.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [33mtid[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0x000056290d7f8460[0m[39m [0m[33mnid[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0x22[0m[39m waiting on condition  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNI global refs: [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m, weak refs: [0m[1;36m1[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a libFuzzer timeout occurring during the fuzzing of PDF text [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction functionality. The timeout happens in the `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod while processing a Type1 font file, specifically at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m where [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`traceConstCmpInt` is called. A patch was attempted that adds consecutive skip [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcount tracking to prevent infinite loops when processing whitespace or NULL bytes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the Type1 lexer. However, after applying the patch, the timeout error persists, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that the patch did not resolve the underlying issue.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack trace shows a timeout occurred at [0m[1;36m28.68[0m[39m seconds during PDF text [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction fuzzing. The main thread is stuck in a RUNNABLE state with the following[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mkey observations:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The execution path shows: `[0m[1;35mPDFExtractTextFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mPDFTextStripper.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → font processing → `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m247[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The timeout occurs during a native method call [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mTraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which is part of the Jazzer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing framework's instrumentation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The main thread consumed approximately [0m[1;36m26778.[0m[39m49ms of CPU time before the timeout[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The thread dump shows normal background threads [0m[1;39m([0m[39mGC, compiler threads, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m all[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctioning properly[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe critical observation is that the main thread is executing within [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m, suggesting either an infinite loop or an [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextremely long-running operation within the token reading logic.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Description[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies `org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Lexer.java` by introducing:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **New class fields:**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `consecutiveSkipCount`: An integer counter to track consecutive skip [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS`: A constant set to [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m as the maximum allowed [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsecutive skips[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Counter reset logic:**[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `consecutiveSkipCount` is reset to [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m whenever a non-skippable token is [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencountered [0m[1;39m([0m[39mopening/closing brackets, parentheses, literals, names, numbers, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Counter increment and validation:**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When whitespace characters are encountered [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m214[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the counter [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrements and checks if it exceeds `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS`[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When NULL bytes are encountered [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m223[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, similar increment and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation occurs[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If the limit is exceeded, a `DamagedFontException` is thrown with a [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdescriptive message[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Counter reset at end of loop:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m273[0m[39m resets the counter before returning null from the method[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch logic aims to prevent infinite loops caused by excessive consecutive [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitespace or NULL bytes by establishing a threshold that, when exceeded, triggers [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man exception.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result Analysis[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the timeout error persists with the same [0m[32m"ERROR: [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mlibFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m message. This indicates that:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Either the patch logic is not being triggered [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe timeout occurs before [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreaching the limit or in a different code path[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The root cause of the timeout is not related to consecutive whitespace or NULL [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbyte processing[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The timeout may be occurring in a different part of the `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min code called from it[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS threshold of [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m may be too high for the fuzzer's [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout settings[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic view of the issue, the following areas should be investigated:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method:** The complete implementation of this method, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparticularly:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The do-while loop structure and all possible execution paths[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Methods called within [0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtryReadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadRegular[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadCharString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Buffer management and position tracking logic[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.getChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method:** Since [0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m repeatedly calls [0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfetch characters, investigate:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How it reads from the ByteBuffer[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether it can enter an infinite loop[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Buffer boundary conditions[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Type1Parser class:** Examine how it calls Type1Lexer:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The [0m[1;35mparseASCII[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method at line [0m[1;36m142[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The [0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method at line [0m[1;36m222[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error handling and recovery mechanisms[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Input data characteristics:** Analyze the fuzzer input that triggers the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Malformed font data patterns[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Buffer sizes and contents[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Specific byte sequences that cause problematic behavior[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **ByteBuffer state management:** Investigate how the buffer position is managed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthroughout the tokenization process and whether position manipulation could cause [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite loops[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Other skip conditions:** The patch only addresses whitespace and NULL bytes, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut there may be other conditions in the code that cause skipping behavior not [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcovered by the patch[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a libFuzzer timeout occurring during PDF text extraction [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing, specifically in the [0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m. A patch was[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted that adds tracking for consecutive skip operations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhitespace and NULL [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a maximum threshold of [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m consecutive skips before throwing an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception. After applying the patch, the timeout persists unchanged, indicating the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch did not address the root cause of the timeout.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer reports a timeout after approximately [0m[1;36m28.68[0m[39m seconds of execution. The [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthread dump reveals the main thread is in a RUNNABLE state, stuck within the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method. The execution path traces through PDF text [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction → font processing → Type1 font parsing → lexical tokenization. The main [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthread consumed [0m[1;36m26778.[0m[39m49ms of CPU time, suggesting active computation rather than [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocking I/O. The timeout occurs at a native method call point [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`traceConstCmpInt`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich is part of Jazzer's instrumentation framework, indicating the timeout [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappened during comparison operations within the tokenization logic.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies Type1Lexer.java by adding a defense mechanism against potential [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite loops caused by excessive consecutive whitespace or NULL bytes. It [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduces a `consecutiveSkipCount` counter and a `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS` constant [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The counter increments when whitespace [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m214[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or NULL bytes [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m223[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are encountered in the do-while loop. When the counter exceeds the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthreshold, a DamagedFontException is thrown. The counter is reset to [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m whenever any[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmeaningful token is identified [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbrackets, parentheses, literals, names, numbers, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39metc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure only consecutive skip operations are counted. The counter is also [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreset before returning null at line [0m[1;36m273[0m[39m.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout error persists after applying the patch, with identical symptoms. This [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicates that either: [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the timeout occurs before the [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m skip threshold is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreached, [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the problematic code path does not involve consecutive whitespace or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNULL bytes, [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the timeout originates from a different location in the call stack,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the threshold value is inappropriate for the timeout duration.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA comprehensive investigation should examine: [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m The complete [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method implementation, including all branches of the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdo-while loop and how the skip flag is managed; [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Methods invoked within [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m such as [0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mtryReadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadRegular[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and [0m   [2m                [0m
