[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m495[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m496[0m[39m:        return null;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m497[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m498[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m499[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m500[0m[39m:     * Reads a binary CharString.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m501[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m502[0m[39m:    private Token [0m[1;35mreadCharString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m503[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m504[0m[39m:        try[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m505[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m506[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mbuffer.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m space[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m507[0m[39m:            byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m data = new byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mlength[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m508[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mbuffer.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m509[0m[39m:            return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, Token.CHARSTRING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m510[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m511[0m[39m:        catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBufferUnderflowException exception[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m512[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m513[0m[39m:            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Premature end of buffer reached"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m514[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m515[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and the evaluation report, I've identified the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause and can now generate a comprehensive fix strategy.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout occurs because `Type1Lexer` contains multiple methods with unbounded [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile loops that accumulate characters into `StringBuilder` objects without any [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength validation. When processing malicious font data containing extremely long [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbillions of consecutive digits, characters, or comment text[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, these [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops can execute for extended periods causing timeouts.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch only addressed consecutive whitespace/NULL bytes in the main [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` loop, but the actual timeout likely occurs in one of the helper [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods that process actual token content:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`[0m[1;35mtryReadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** - Three separate while loops reading digits [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m271[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m276[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m318[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m322[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m351[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m355[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **`[0m[1;35mreadRegular[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** - While loop reading non-delimiter characters [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m382[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m400[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **`[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** - While loop reading comment text [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m414[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m425[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **`[0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** - While loop reading string content [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m436[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m495[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe solution follows the established pattern in `BaseParser` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1445[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1455[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich implements StringBuilder length checks inside digit-reading loops. This [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapproach:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents unbounded memory growth[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Detects malicious input early[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses existing `DamagedFontException` for consistency[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Allows legitimate font files to process normally[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Implementation Steps[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Add Maximum Length Constants**[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd the following constants to the `Type1Lexer` class [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m[1;36m54[0m[39m, alongside [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting fields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate static final int MAX_NUMBER_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate static final int MAX_NAME_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m1000[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate static final int MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate static final int MAX_STRING_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m5000000[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese limits are:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Generous enough for legitimate fonts [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtest cases show much smaller values[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Based on similar patterns in `BaseParser.MAX_LENGTH_LONG` and [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`PfbParser.MAX_LENGTH`[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Sufficient to prevent timeout attacks while allowing normal operation[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Protect `[0m[1;35mtryReadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Method**[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd length checks after EVERY `[0m[1;35msb.append[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call in the three digit-reading while [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **First loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m271[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m276[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:** After line [0m[1;36m273[0m[39m, add:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msb.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > MAX_NUMBER_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Number is too long, exceeds maximum length: "[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ MAX_NUMBER_LENGTH + [0m[32m" at position "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Second loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m318[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m322[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:** After line [0m[1;36m320[0m[39m, add the same check[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Third loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m351[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m355[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:** After line [0m[1;36m353[0m[39m, add the same check[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAlso add checks after the optional character appends:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m266[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'+'[0m[39m or [0m[32m'-'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m281[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'.'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m307[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending digit after decimal/radix[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m327[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'E'[0m[39m or [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m333[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'-'[0m[39m in exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m340[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending digit in exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Protect `[0m[1;35mreadRegular[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Method**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd a length check in the while loop after line [0m[1;36m398[0m[39m:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msb.append[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msb.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > MAX_NAME_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Name token is too long, exceeds maximum length:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m[39m + MAX_NAME_LENGTH + [0m[32m" at position "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Protect `[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Method**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd a length check in the while loop after line [0m[1;36m423[0m[39m:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msb.append[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msb.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Comment is too long, exceeds maximum length: "[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH + [0m[32m" at position "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Protect `[0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Method**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd length checks after EVERY `[0m[1;35msb.append[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call in the switch statement:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m445[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'[0m[32m([0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m453[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'[0m[32m)[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m462[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m"\n"[0m[39m for [0m[32m'n'[0m[39m or [0m[32m'r'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m463[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'\t'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m464[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'\b'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m465[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'\f'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m466[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending '\\'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m467[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'[0m[32m([0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m468[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m'[0m[32m)[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m479[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending octal character[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m489[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending [0m[32m"\n"[0m[39m for [0m[32m'\r'[0m[39m or [0m[32m'\n'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m492[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mappending default character[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEach check should be:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msb.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > MAX_STRING_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"String is too long, exceeds maximum length: "[0m[39m +[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_STRING_LENGTH + [0m[32m" at position "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mbuffer.position[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Remove Previous Patch**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch added `consecutiveSkipCount` tracking in `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. This [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapproach should be **removed entirely** because:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It doesn't address the root cause [0m[1;39m([0m[39munbounded token content accumulation[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The checks in helper methods will prevent timeouts more effectively[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It adds unnecessary complexity and state management[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The limit of [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m was insufficient and arbitrary[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemove:[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `consecutiveSkipCount` and `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_SKIPS` fields [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines added in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevious patch[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All counter increment/reset logic added to `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All checks that throw exceptions based on `consecutiveSkipCount`[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why This is Optimal:**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Follows Established Patterns:** Mirrors the approach in [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mBaseParser.readLong[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which successfully prevents similar issues[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Comprehensive Coverage:** Protects all vulnerable code paths, not just [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitespace handling[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Early Detection:** Catches problems during token accumulation rather than [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter timeout[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Preserves Functionality:** Limits are generous enough for all legitimate fonts[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Consistent Error Handling:** Uses existing `DamagedFontException` already [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrown at lines [0m[1;36m164[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m223[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **No Breaking Changes:** All existing test cases pass [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtest tokens are well [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder limits[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How It Preserves Existing Logic:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No changes to token parsing logic or semantics[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No modifications to buffer management or position tracking[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No alterations to delimiter detection or token type identification[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintains all existing error handling paths[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Supports all PostScript number formats [0m[1;39m([0m[39mintegers, reals, radix notation, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscientific notation[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How It Addresses the Issue:**[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents unbounded loops by limiting StringBuilder growth[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throws exceptions early when detecting malicious input[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Provides clear error messages with buffer positions for debugging[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stops processing before timeout can occur[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Works for all types of excessive input [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdigits, characters, comments, strings[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential Side Effects and Mitigation:**[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Side Effect:** Legitimate but unusually large tokens might be rejected[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation:** The limits are set very generously [0m[1;39m([0m[39m5MB for strings, 100K for [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomments[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m based on typical font structure and test analysis[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Side Effect:** Error messages change from timeout to DamagedFontException[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation:** This is actually an improvement - provides clearer indication of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe problem and where it occurred[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Side Effect:** Performance overhead from length checks[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation:** Minimal - simple integer comparison after each character append, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnegligible compared to StringBuilder operations[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Similar Solutions in Codebase:**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mBaseParser.readLong[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` uses identical pattern for number parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1445[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1455[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `PfbParser` uses size validation for overall file size [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m156[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m164[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Both demonstrate this is the established approach for preventing resource [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexhaustion in this codebase[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reports a libFuzzer timeout occurring during PDF text extraction.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout happens in the Type1Lexer.readToken method while processing font data, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifically during a constant comparison operation. The patch attempt adds length [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimits to various token types [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumbers, names, comments[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the Type1Lexer class to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent potential infinite loops or excessive processing. However, after applying [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch, the timeout error persists, indicating that the patch does not resolve [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe underlying issue.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack trace reveals that the timeout occurs in the main thread during the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution of `org.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Lexer.readToken` at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m. The call [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchain shows:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer is testing PDF text extraction through [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`PDFExtractTextFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The extraction process loads a Type1 font via `PDType1Font.<init>` and [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Type1Font.createWithPFB`[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The Type1Parser is parsing the ASCII section and reading encoding information[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The Type1Lexer.nextToken method calls readToken, which appears to be stuck at [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m247[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Notably, the timeout is triggered during a native method call [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt`, which suggests the issue occurs [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring a comparison operation[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe thread dump shows the main thread has consumed [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m778.[0m[39m49ms of CPU time in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapproximately [0m[1;36m28.68[0m[39m seconds of elapsed time, indicating an intensive computation is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurring. The thread is in a RUNNABLE state, actively consuming CPU resources [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrather than waiting on I/O or locks.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Details[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch introduces four static constants to limit token lengths:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_NUMBER_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m`: Limits numeric token length[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_NAME_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m1000[0m[39m`: Limits name token length  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m`: Limits comment length[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_STRING_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m5000000[0m[39m`: Defined but not used in the provided patch[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies the `[0m[1;35mreadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mreadName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods by adding length [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks after each character append operation. Specifically:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In the `[0m[1;35mreadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, checks are added after appending:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Sign characters [0m[1;39m([0m[32m'+'[0m[39m or [0m[32m'-'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Digit characters in the integer part[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Decimal point [0m[1;39m([0m[32m'.'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Digit characters in the fractional part[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Exponent indicator [0m[1;39m([0m[32m'E'[0m[39m or [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Exponent sign[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Exponent digits[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In the `[0m[1;35mreadName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, a check is added after appending each character to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe StringBuilder[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. In the `[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, a check is added after appending each character[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen any limit is exceeded, a `DamagedFontException` is thrown with a descriptive [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessage including the limit and buffer position.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch does not resolve the timeout issue. The error message remains identical: [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m. This indicates that either:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout is occurring in a different code path not covered by the patch[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout occurs before any of the length limits are reached[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The issue is not related to excessive token length but rather to a different type[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof infinite loop or intensive computation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Type1Lexer.readToken method at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m**: The stack trace specifically points[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto this line. The complete implementation of this method should be examined to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand what operation is performed at this exact line and why it might enter an[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite loop or intensive computation.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Type1Lexer.readString method**: The patch defines `MAX_STRING_LENGTH` but does[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot add any checks for string token parsing. Since strings can be much longer than [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother token types [0m[1;39m([0m[39m5MB limit vs [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m characters for numbers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, this could be a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignificant oversight.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Character comparison logic**: The native callback `traceConstCmpInt` in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack trace suggests the timeout occurs during an integer comparison operation. The[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomparison logic in readToken around line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m should be investigated.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Buffer positioning and loop termination conditions**: The various read methods[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min Type1Lexer use `[0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to advance through the buffer. The termination [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditions for loops in these methods should be examined to ensure they cannot loop[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindefinitely on malformed input.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Type1Parser.readEncoding method**: This is the calling context for the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblematic readToken call. Understanding what encoding data is being parsed and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhow readToken is being used in this context may provide insights.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Input data characteristics**: The fuzzer-generated input that triggers the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout should be analyzed to understand what specific byte patterns or font [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure causes the problematic behavior.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and evaluation report, I've identified the root [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause of the timeout issue:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout occurs due to an **infinite loop in the `readToken` method's control [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflow structure**. The method has a problematic nested loop:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdo [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    skip = false;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Process characters[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Set skip = true for whitespace/null bytes[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**The infinite loop scenario:**[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. When the buffer ends with whitespace [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m199[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or null byte [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m201[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m204[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m125[0m[39m consumes the last character[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. `skip` is set to `true`[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Inner `while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` exits because buffer is exhausted[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Outer `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m evaluates to `true`, continues[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Inner loop condition evaluates to `false` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuffer empty[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, body never executes[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Control returns to line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m, creating an infinite loop[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why Previous Patch Failed[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch added length limits to `[0m[1;35mreadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods. However:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout doesn't occur **within** these methods[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It occurs in the **outer control flow** of `readToken` itself[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The infinite loop happens when the buffer is exhausted with `[0m[33mskip[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m`, before [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many token reading method is called[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Length limits cannot prevent a control flow issue where no data accumulation is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappening[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Fix Strategy[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix must ensure that when the buffer is exhausted, `readToken` returns `null` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately, regardless of the `skip` flag value. There are two approaches:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Approach [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRecommended[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Check buffer state in outer loop condition**[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m to check both `skip` AND `[0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis ensures the outer loop only continues if:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- We need to skip whitespace/null bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`skip` is true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AND[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- There's more data to process [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is true[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Approach [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Add explicit check after inner loop**[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd a check after the inner loop exits to immediately return null if buffer is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexhausted:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m end of inner while[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return null;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m end of do[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Implementation Details[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Recommended: Approach [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m** is cleaner and follows the pattern established by other[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread methods. The fix should:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Locate line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m in [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Lexer.java`[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Change `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` to `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis single-line change ensures:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- When buffer is exhausted, the method returns `null` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m248[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m regardless of [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`skip` state[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Normal whitespace/null-byte skipping still works when more data is available[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fix is minimal and doesn't add complexity[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It respects the contract expected by callers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturn `null` when no more tokens[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Justification[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Optimal approach**: This is a minimal, surgical fix targeting the exact root [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserves existing logic**: [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whitespace/null-byte skipping still works correctly when buffer has data[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All token parsing methods remain unchanged[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No impact on normal parsing behavior[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Addresses the issue**: [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Prevents infinite loop when buffer ends with whitespace/null bytes[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Returns `null` as expected by the parser when no more tokens available[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **No side effects**:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The change only affects the termination condition of the outer loop[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When buffer is exhausted, returning `null` is the correct behavior[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests should continue to pass[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Similar patterns**: Other read methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`readRegular`, `readComment`, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`readString`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m all exit cleanly when `[0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is false[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential concern**: Could this change affect behavior when skipping trailing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitespace?[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: No, because:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If buffer has more data after whitespace, `[0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is true, loop [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinues normally[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If buffer is exhausted, there are no more tokens to return anyway, so returning [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`null` is correct[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The parser expects `null` when no more tokens are available[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Testing**: The fix should not break any existing tests because:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m of the test cases test buffers ending with whitespace/null bytes[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fix only changes behavior in the previously-broken edge case[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Normal token parsing and whitespace skipping remain identical[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue manifests as a libFuzzer timeout after approximately [0m[1;36m28.68[0m[39m [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseconds of execution. The thread dump reveals:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Main Thread State**: The main thread [0m[1;39m([0m[33mtid[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0x000056290d69db70[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is in RUNNABLE [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Stack Trace Location**: The execution is stuck at [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35morg.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mType1Lexer.jav[0m[1;92ma:247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Call Chain**: The problematic call originates from PDF text extraction: [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mPDFTextStripper.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → font processing → `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → [0m            [2m                [0m
