[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Native Instrumentation**: The trace shows [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mTraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNative Method[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is involved, which [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis part of Jazzer's fuzzing instrumentation[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Description[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch introduced several defensive measures to the `Type1Lexer.java` file:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Maximum Length Constants**: Added four constants at the class level:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_NUMBER_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m`[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_NAME_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m1000[0m[39m`[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m`[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_STRING_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m5000000[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdeclared but not used in the visible patch[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Loop Termination Condition**: Modified line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m in the `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changed `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` to `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This adds an explicit buffer boundary check to prevent infinite loops[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Length Validation in Number Parsing**: Added validation checks in the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mbuildNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at multiple points where characters are appended to the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStringBuilder. Each check throws a `DamagedFontException` when `[0m[1;35msb.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_NUMBER_LENGTH`[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Length Validation in Name Parsing**: Added validation in the `[0m[1;35mbuildName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod to prevent names exceeding `MAX_NAME_LENGTH`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Length Validation in Comment Parsing**: Added validation in the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mbuildComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to prevent comments exceeding `MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the timeout issue persists. The error message remains [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m with no additional details, suggesting that:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout still occurs within the same general area of code[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The added constraints either don't address the root cause or the problematic path[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbypasses them[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The buffer check modification `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` may not be [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msufficient[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Type1Lexer.java - [0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method**: The complete logic of the [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method around line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m needs examination, particularly:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All conditions that control the `skip` variable in the do-while loop[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Character comparison operations that might trigger the fuzzer's [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstrumentation[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential infinite loop conditions that aren't covered by the buffer check[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Type1Lexer.java - [0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method**: This method is called frequently during [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoken reading and may contribute to the issue:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Buffer position advancement logic[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Return values when buffer is exhausted[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any internal state that could cause [0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to return values that perpetuate[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Type1Parser.java - [0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method**: Located at line [0m[1;36m222[0m[39m in the stack [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrace, this method calls `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` repeatedly:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Loop conditions in the encoding parsing logic[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Token validation and error handling[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - State machine logic that might not properly handle malformed input[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Input Data Characteristics**: The fuzzer-generated input that triggers this [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout should be analyzed:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Specific byte patterns in the PFB [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPostScript Font Binary[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m file[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Token sequences that lead to the problematic state[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Edge cases in Type1 font encoding definitions[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Token State Management**: The interaction between `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and the `aheadToken` field:[0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Conditions under which tokens are consumed versus retained[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - State consistency during error conditions[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Character Classification Logic**: The code extensively uses [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCharacter.isDigit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mCharacter.isWhitespace[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and custom character checks:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All branches in character classification[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential edge cases with special characters or invalid byte sequences[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Interaction between character reading and buffer position management[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch addressed symptom-level issues by adding length limits, but the core [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblem—what causes the code to loop excessively in the first place—remains [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munresolved.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1445[0m[39m:        int lastByte;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1446[0m[39m:        StringBuilder buffer = new [0m[1;35mStringBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1447[0m[39m:        while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35misDigit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlastByte = [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1448[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1449[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mbuffer.append[0m[1;39m([0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mlastByte [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1450[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbuffer.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > MAX_LENGTH_LONG[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1451[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1452[0m[39m:                throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Number '"[0m[39m + buffer + [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1453[0m[39m:                        [0m[32m"' is getting too long, stop reading at offset "[0m[39m + [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msource.getPosition[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1454[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1455[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/pfb/PfbParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:66[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m72[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:    private static final int EOF_MARKER = [0m[1;36m0x03[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:     * Heuristically chosen max length to buffer a Type1 font[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:    private static final long MAX_LENGTH = 100_000_000;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code and evaluation report, I've identified the root cause of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe timeout issue:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout occurs in the `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method's do-while loop structure. The [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblem has two components:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Missing `skip = true` after comment processing**: When a [0m[32m'%'[0m[39m comment delimiter[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis encountered [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m131[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, `[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called to consume the comment, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut the code does NOT set `skip = true` afterward. This is inconsistent with how [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitespace and null bytes are handled [0m[1;39m([0m[39mboth set `skip = true`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Unsafe loop termination condition**: The outer loop at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m uses `while [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` without checking if the buffer has remaining data. This can cause issues [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer is exhausted after processing comments[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `skip` flag is in an inconsistent state[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer instrumentation interferes with the loop condition[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why the Previous Patch Failed[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch attempted to:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add maximum length constraints for tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumbers, names, comments[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add a buffer check `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m247[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, the patch didn't address the core issue: **comments are not marked as [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mskippable content**. Without setting `skip = true` after processing comments, the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop logic remains broken.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### The Complete Fix Strategy[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix requires two changes to `Type1Lexer.java`:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Set `skip = true` after reading comments** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m131[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After `[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns, add `skip = true;` on the next line[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This makes comment handling consistent with whitespace and null byte handling[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Comments are skippable content and should trigger a retry to find the next [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmeaningful token[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Add buffer exhaustion check to loop condition** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` to `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This provides a defensive termination condition[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Prevents infinite loops when [0m[33mskip[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m but buffer is exhausted[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Addresses the specific line where the fuzzer detected the timeout[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Implementation Details[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Change [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add skip flag after comment processing**[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLocation: After line [0m[1;36m131[0m[39m in the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'%'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'%'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m comment[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    skip = true;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m ← Add this line[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Change [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Update loop termination condition**[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLocation: Line [0m[1;36m247[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m ← Change from while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addresses the root cause**: Comments should be treated as skippable content, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjust like whitespace and null bytes[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Maintains consistency**: All three types of skippable content [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhitespace, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull bytes, comments[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m now follow the same pattern[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves existing logic**: The fix doesn't change how tokens are parsed or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturned, only how skippable content is handled[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Adds defensive programming**: The buffer exhaustion check prevents infinite [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops in edge cases[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Minimal changes**: Only two lines need to be modified, reducing the risk of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroducing new bugs[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **No arbitrary limits needed**: Unlike the previous patch, we don't need maximum[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength constraints for individual token types, as the buffer exhaustion check [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprovides sufficient protection[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect**: After processing comments, the outer loop will retry once more [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore potentially returning null[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: This is the intended behavior - comments should not terminate token[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading, they should be skipped like whitespace[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect**: The loop will terminate earlier when buffer is exhausted[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: This is correct behavior - when there's no more data, the method [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould return null rather than looping indefinitely[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Evaluation Report Issues[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Timeout at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m**: The buffer exhaustion check prevents infinite loops at [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis exact location[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Fuzzer instrumentation interference**: By adding an explicit termination [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcondition, we reduce the complexity of the loop condition that the fuzzer [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstruments[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Comment handling without newlines**: Comments that extend to the buffer end [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill now properly set [0m[33mskip[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m and terminate via the buffer exhaustion check[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Consistent behavior**: All skippable content now follows the same code pattern[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Main Thread State**: The main thread is in a RUNNABLE state, stuck at line [0m[1;36m247[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Call Chain**: The execution path shows:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mPDFExtractTextFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzzer entry point[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Through PDFBox text extraction pipeline[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Font loading via `PDType1Font` constructor[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Type1 font parsing via `[0m[1;35mType1Parser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Token reading in `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Native Callback**: The stack trace shows a call to [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mTraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNative Method[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m immediately [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore `[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, indicating the fuzzer's instrumentation is active [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat this point[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **High CPU Usage**: The main thread consumed [0m[1;36m26778.[0m[39m49ms of CPU time, suggesting [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mactive computation rather than blocking I/O[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Context**: The timeout occurs during encoding parsing [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mType1Parser.readEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m222[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Description[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch introduced several defensive measures to the `Type1Lexer` class:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Constants Added**:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_NUMBER_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m`: Maximum allowed length for numeric tokens[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_NAME_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m1000[0m[39m`: Maximum allowed length for name tokens[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH = [0m[1;36m100000[0m[39m`: Maximum allowed length for comment tokens[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Comment Reading Modification** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m133[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m136[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added `skip = true;` after `[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures the outer loop in `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` continues after processing a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomment[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Loop Termination Condition Change** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline ~[0m[1;36m249[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m252[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original: `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modified: `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This adds an explicit buffer boundary check to prevent infinite loops[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Length Checks in `[0m[1;35mreadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method**:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added bounds checking after each character append operation[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throws `DamagedFontException` when `MAX_NUMBER_LENGTH` is exceeded[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Multiple insertion points throughout the method covering all numeric parsing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths [0m[1;39m([0m[39msign, digits, decimal point, exponent notation[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Length Check in `[0m[1;35mreadName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m437[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m442[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added bounds checking during name token construction[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throws `DamagedFontException` when `MAX_NAME_LENGTH` is exceeded[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Length Check in `[0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m466[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m471[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added bounds checking during comment reading[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throws `DamagedFontException` when `MAX_COMMENT_LENGTH` is exceeded[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Post-Patch Results[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the timeout still occurs with similar characteristics:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Persistent Timeout**: The timeout still happens after approximately [0m[1;36m28.71[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseconds[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Different Stack Position**: The main thread is now stuck at [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` line [0m[1;36m75[0m[39m, rather than `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` line [0m[1;36m247[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Similar CPU Usage**: Main thread consumed [0m[1;36m26447.[0m[39m74ms CPU time [0m[1;39m([0m[39mslightly less [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut still very high[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Same Call Chain**: The execution path remains identical through the PDFBox [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Notable Absence**: The native callback [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceConstCmpInt`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m no longer appears in the stack [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrace before the `Type1Lexer` methods[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack trace shows the thread is stuck in the `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, which [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuggests the infinite loop may be occurring at a higher level in the token reading [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic rather than within individual token type readers.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method**: The main loop structure at line [0m[1;36m75[0m[39m should be [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexamined to understand what conditions could cause it to loop indefinitely, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mespecially given the buffer boundary check was added to the `[0m[1;35mreadToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mType1Lexer.readToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method**: The complete logic of the do-while loop and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall possible paths through the `skip` variable logic need detailed analysis, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparticularly:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All conditions that set or reset the `skip` flag[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interaction between different token types [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomments, parentheses, names, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumbers[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `openParens` counter logic and how it affects loop termination[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mType1Parser.readEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method**: At line [0m[1;36m222[0m[39m, this method calls into the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlexer and may have its own loop structures that interact with the lexer's token [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Buffer Management**: The `ByteBuffer buffer` member and how it's consumed [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring token reading, particularly:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether `[0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` correctly reflects the buffer state[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `[0m[1;35mgetChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mputBack[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods manipulate buffer position[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Edge cases where buffer might appear to have content but creates parsing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mambiguity[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Token Lookahead Logic**: The `aheadToken` member variable and how it interacts[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the main token reading loop in `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Character Classification**: The delimiters and whitespace handling logic that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetermines token boundaries, as malformed input might create scenarios where tokens[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare never properly terminated[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Input Data Characteristics**: The specific fuzzer input that triggers this [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout should be analyzed to understand what font structure patterns cause the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fact that the timeout persists after adding explicit bounds checks and loop [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtermination conditions suggests the infinite loop occurs through a logical path not[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcovered by the patch, possibly involving state management or interactions between [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiple methods in the token reading pipeline.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Updated Analysis with Retrieved Code[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod patterns. Now I have complete context to finalize the fix strategy.[0m          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:140[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m165[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis shows how `[0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called and the surrounding context. The method [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis called from within a switch statement during dictionary parsing.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Final Fix Strategy[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Fix: Add null token check in [0m[1;35mType1Parser.readEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.jav[0m[1;92ma:217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[39m`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Detailed Implementation:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe problematic loop structure needs to be modified to handle null tokens properly.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix should:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Add null check in the while loop condition:**[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before evaluating the complex condition, check if `[0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m != null`[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents the loop from continuing when tokens are exhausted[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Add validation after the loop:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After the loop exits, verify that we exited because we found the expected [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoken, not because of null[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throw `IOException` if we hit null before finding [0m[32m"dup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"readonly"[0m[39m, or [0m[32m"def"[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Modified code structure:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Skip tokens until we find [0m[32m"dup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"readonly"[0m[39m, or [0m[32m"def"[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m != null && [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"dup"[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"readonly"[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"def"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Verify we found the expected token, not just ran out of tokens[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Unexpected end of file while reading encoding, expected [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'dup', 'readonly', or 'def'"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale:**[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The null check in the while condition prevents infinite looping[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The post-loop validation ensures we don't silently skip past incomplete encoding [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msections[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error message is descriptive and consistent with other IOException messages [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the codebase[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This pattern is already used elsewhere in Type1Parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., lines [0m[1;36m119[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m123[0m[39m, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m334[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m337[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m397[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m399[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'%'[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mreadComment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       skip = true;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m ADD THIS LINE[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Add buffer check to outer loop condition [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip && [0m[1;35mbuffer.hasRemaining[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Modified from: while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Add length checks in [0m[1;35mreadNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method** - Multiple locations throughout the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod after each `[0m[1;35msb.append[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Complete Solution Works[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Fixes the Root Cause**: The parser-level null check prevents the infinite loop[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat was causing the timeout[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Defensive Programming**: The lexer-level fixes prevent other potential issues:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Excessive memory consumption from malformed tokens[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Unpredictable behavior from comment handling[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Buffer overrun scenarios[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Consistent Error Handling**: [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All error cases throw descriptive exceptions[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error messages include position information for debugging[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Follows existing patterns in the codebase[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
